399:  Direct from \lstinline{CategoryTheory.Abelian.Ext.linearEquiv₀} applied to the abelian category $\Sheaf(J, \ModuleCat\,k)$, which is $\Linear k$-enriched (auto-inferable from the prerequisites of Section~\ref{sec:moduleK_prereqs}) and has $\HasExt$ (Theorem~\ref{thm:HasExt_Sheaf_Opens_ModuleCatK}). The $\noncomputable$ \lstinline{abbrev} reducibility of $\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,0\,X$ (Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_HModule_prime}) lets instance synthesis unfold the wrapper to the underlying $\Ext^0$ group, and \lstinline{linearEquiv₀} returns the $\Module k$-linear bijection between that $\Ext^0$ group and the corresponding Hom group in the sheaf category. The closure body is therefore a one-liner \lstinline{Abelian.Ext.linearEquiv₀}; iter-015 plan-agent \lstinline{lean_run_code} probe confirms the closure compiles end-to-end against current Mathlib + project state, kernel-only axioms.
