433:The \emph{codomain remains $\AddCommGrpCat$}, not $\ModuleCat\,k$, because Mathlib's $\Abelian.\mathtt{extFunctor}\,n \,\colon\, \Cop \Longrightarrow C \Longrightarrow \AddCommGrpCat$ always lands in $\AddCommGrpCat$, regardless of which $\Linear k$-enriched abelian category we start in. (A genuinely $\ModuleCat\,k$-valued analog would require a new $\mathtt{linearExtFunctor}$ that Mathlib does not have; we do not introduce it here.) The per-fiber $\Module\,k$ structure on the evaluation $(\HModulePrime\_\mathtt{cohomologyPresheaf}\,k\,F\,n).\mathrm{obj}\,(\mathrm{op}\,X)$ is preserved through the iter-014 $\HModulePrime$ reducibility: the underlying $\Type\,u$ matches $\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,X$ definitionally (probe-confirmed \lstinline{rfl}), and that carries the $\Module\,k$ inherited from $\Abelian.\Ext.\mathtt{instModule}$ via the $\Linear\,k$ enrichment.
